# TriageOps core

Read `AGENTS.md` for setup and phase status. Human docs live in `docs/`.

## Principles

- Smallest correct diff; match surrounding code style.
- No commits, PRs, or doc updates unless the user asks.
- Extend existing helpers (`lib/services/`, `lib/queue.ts`, worker `lib/`) before adding parallel abstractions.

## Monorepo

| Package | Role |
|---------|------|
| `apps/web` | Next.js dashboard + API routes |
| `apps/worker` | BullMQ workers (sync, LLM) |
| `packages/db` | Prisma schema + client |
| `packages/metrics` | Pure triage metric functions |
| `packages/shared-types` | Queue names + job payloads |

## Commands

```bash
npm run docker:up && npm run db:migrate
npm run dev          # web
npm run dev:worker   # workers
npm test && npm run build -w @triage-ops/web
```

After schema changes: `npm run db:generate` and restart dev servers if Prisma types are stale.
